<h1>@HI{{owaru}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> V@masustem{{}} @HI{{<strong>owaru</strong>}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{owaru}}</strong> functions as a auxiliary verb attached to the @HI{{masu}} stem of a verb and gives the meaning of "finish doing ~".
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{[@KJ{{source^family*name^thing^word}}]wo yatto @KJ{{read}}mi@KJ{{end}}warimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I finally finished reading <em>The Tale of the Genji</em>.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
In writing <strong>@HI{{owaru}}</strong> can be replaced by @HI{{oeru}}.
</p>

